                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> The trapped door is opened other than by a serpentfolk</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> Hissing, illusionary snakes leap from the door. Each living creature within 30 feet is subjected to the curse of potent poison. If a living creature opened the door, that creature must roll its saving throw against the curse twice and take the worse result (this is a misfortune effect).</p>\n<hr />\n<h3>Curse of Potent Poison (uncommon, curse, magical) CURSE 5</h3>\n<p>This curse magically speeds poison through your body.</p>\n<p><strong>Saving Throw</strong> @Check[type:will|dc:20|name:Curse of Potent Poison|traits:uncommon,magical]</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> You take a -1 status penalty to Fortitude saves and you gain weakness 3 to poison (if you already have weakness to poison, increase it by 3). The curse remains until removed by <em>@Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.Remove Curse]{Remove Curse}</em> or similar magic.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[pf2e.equipment-effects.Effect: Curse of Potent Poison]{Effect: Curse of Potent Poison}</p>"
